  <brief_title>A Comparison of the Safety and Efficacy of Cefdinir Oral Suspension Versus Amoxicillin/Clavulanate in Pediatric Subjects With Acute Otitis Media</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Comparison of the Safety and Efficacy of Cefdinir Oral Suspension Versus Amoxicillin/Clavulanate in Pediatric Subjects With Acute Otitis Media</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Abbott</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Abbott</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The primary objective is to compare the safety and efficacy of cefdinir oral suspension, 7
      mg/kg/day ql2hrs for 5 days, to amoxicillin/clavulanate oral suspension 45 mg/kg/day (based
      on amoxicillin component), in divided doses, q12h for 10 days, in children between 6 months
      and 6 years of age, with AOM.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
